Gov. AbdulRahman AbdulRazaq of Kwara has urged members of the All Progressives Congress (APC) to double efforts towards victory in the March 11 polls in the state. He enjoined them to canvass for votes from all eligible voters to guarantee the success of the party in the Governorship and House of Assembly elections. AAbdulRazaq made the appeal on Sunday at APC Adewole Ward meeting in Ilorin West Local Government Area of Kwara. “We must not relent because of the success recorded in previous elections. We must redouble our efforts to consolidate on the success. ‘We must continue to canvass and campaign for our party and all our candidates. We must all come out and vote next Saturday. “I want to call on all APC stakeholders, elders, women and youth groups to continue the campaign to ensure the victory of the party,” AbdulRazaq tasked the meeting. The governor however congratulated the party faithful and all residents of the state for ensuring the success of the APC at the Presidential and National Assembly elections on Feb. 25. “I want to congratulate you for the success recorded in the Presidential and National Assembly elections. “We are glad that Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu and all our National Assembly candidates emerged victorious in the polls,” he said. The governor called on party supporters to be peaceful and wary of the opposition elements who may want to disrupt the electoral process. “By the grace of God, we will win the Saturday Governorship and House of Assembly elections. “The opposition knows they can’t win this election but bent on disrupting the process. Don’t allow that, come out peacefully and ensure that you vote for APC massively. “Don’t resort to violence. We shall win this election, In-Shaa Allah,” said AbdulRazaq. 